My daughter is a prisoner
in her own Kingdom.

20:46.579 --> 20:49.742
You are the Queen's father?

20:50.417 --> 20:52.453
Please, take this to her.

20:52.544 --> 20:55.126
The Palace Guards won't allow me
into her chambers.

20:55.463 --> 20:57.328
They know I'd die for her.

20:57.924 --> 21:01.291
But you. The King trusts you.

21:02.137 --> 21:04.879
He doesn't know
that you have my daughter's heart.

21:04.973 --> 21:06.634
The guards will allow you in.

21:07.183 --> 21:08.389
Give her this box.

21:08.476 --> 21:10.717
Wait, I don't understand.
What is in it?

21:10.812 --> 21:13.349
This is the only thing
that can free her

21:14.274 --> 21:15.810
from this wretched life.

21:16.443 --> 21:18.479
If you truly care for my daughter,

21:19.487 --> 21:23.651
I know you'll do whatever it takes
to set her free.

21:45.847 --> 21:47.462
What are we doing here?

21:47.682 --> 21:50.139
We know she bought land from Gold,
we don't know why.

21:50.226 --> 21:51.477
I'm willing to bet
it's for personal reasons,

21:51.561 --> 21:52.641
but we have to know for sure.

21:52.729 --> 21:54.560
We need documents that officially
link her to that land.

21:54.647 --> 21:56.148
So you want to break into her office?

21:56.524 --> 21:59.641
It's locked and she's got a state of
the art security system and alarm.

21:59.736 --> 22:02.102
If we don't show this town
who Regina really is, who will?

22:02.197 --> 22:04.404
-Do you think you can crack her code?
-Yep.

22:04.491 --> 22:05.480
(ALARM SOUNDING)

22:05.575 --> 22:06.735
Emma!

22:06.826 --> 22:09.863
Who does the alarm system alert?
The police. I'm the police.

22:09.954 --> 22:11.569
Two minutes for her to
get a call from the alarm company,

22:11.664 --> 22:14.280
one minute to get her coat and keys,
three minutes to drive here.

22:14.375 --> 22:16.411
-We got maybe six minutes.
-(SIGHS)

22:20.882 --> 22:22.292
(ALARM CONTIN U ES)

22:25.762 --> 22:27.502
(BEEPING)

22:30.517 --> 22:32.724
I just uncovered every file
that references

22:32.810 --> 22:34.550
the tract of land
she bought from Gold.

22:38.066 --> 22:39.181
Nice!

22:44.739 --> 22:46.275
What the hell do these open?

22:46.366 --> 22:47.401
I don't know.

22:50.286 --> 22:51.822
-What are you doing?
-Looking for Henry's book.

22:51.913 --> 22:53.653
We didn't come here for Henry.
We came here for the files...

22:53.748 --> 22:57.081
No, you didn't come here for Henry.
Me, that's the only reason I'm here.

22:59.796 --> 23:00.956
Oh!

23:02.507 --> 23:03.917
-What are you doing?
-(KEYS BEEPING)

23:04.008 --> 23:05.088
-Some kids broke in.
-(ALARM STOPS)

23:05.176 --> 23:08.668
I heard the alarm so I'm checking it out,
'cause I'm Sheriff.

23:10.265 --> 23:12.256
Well, that was
an awfully quick response time.

23:12.517 --> 23:14.599
You told me to do myjob
and I'm doing it.

23:15.937 --> 23:16.892
And you brought him?

23:16.980 --> 23:18.811
Oh, well, he saw it
while he was on a walk.

23:18.898 --> 23:20.308
So he's a witness.

23:20.400 --> 23:21.560
Mmm.

23:21.651 --> 23:23.107
And what did you see, Sidney?

23:24.445 --> 23:25.946
Some kids with a...

23:26.030 --> 23:27.736
-Rock.
-A rock.

23:29.784 --> 23:31.115
Did they take anything?

23:31.202 --> 23:34.410
I don't know, I'd have to
do a thorough sweep to find out.

23:35.582 --> 23:37.368
It appears to me
it's all just a prank.

23:37.458 --> 23:39.449
You sure you don't want me to
take the place apart?

23:41.254 --> 23:43.711
Sheriff, your services are not wanted
norneeded.

23:43.798 --> 23:44.787
Okay.

23:44.882 --> 23:46.622
Well, you know where to find me.

24:07.155 --> 24:08.645
It's you!

24:09.449 --> 24:10.780
Oh.

24:17.332 --> 24:20.824
My love for you grows stronger
with every beat of my heart.

24:23.504 --> 24:25.665
But the King has read my diary,

24:25.965 --> 24:27.341
found my mirror.

24:27.425 --> 24:30.292
Soon, he will discover
the truth about us.

24:30.428 --> 24:31.838
There is no escape.

24:31.929 --> 24:34.671
There is always an escape.

24:39.103 --> 24:41.185
would give you your freedom.

24:47.862 --> 24:49.693
QUEEN: Yes. I believe it will.

24:54.952 --> 24:56.203
(HISSING)

25:02.543 --> 25:04.329
The Agrabahn viper.

25:05.046 --> 25:07.162
A snake so deadly
it can kill anything.

25:07.256 --> 25:09.542
With a single bite.

25:10.051 --> 25:12.383
This serpent is from my homeland.

25:13.096 --> 25:14.427
I know all too well of its poison.

25:14.555 --> 25:15.965
But why would you
have it brought here?

25:17.892 --> 25:21.134
There is no happiness left for me
in this life.

25:21.688 --> 25:23.519
One small bite,

25:24.065 --> 25:26.807
and I shall be
free from this prison forever.

25:29.904 --> 25:32.646
I'm sorry we couldn't be together,
my love.

25:35.076 --> 25:38.284
Perhaps in another life
we will find each other again.

25:50.633 --> 25:53.966
There is another way.

25:54.971 --> 25:59.681
What if the King didn't live?

26:04.981 --> 26:06.596
You would do that for me?

26:06.941 --> 26:09.478
For you I would do anything.

26:12.071 --> 26:13.481
(SIGHING)

26:15.908 --> 26:18.115
I don't know what I'd do without you.

26:18.619 --> 26:20.951
You will never have to find out.

26:28.463 --> 26:29.828
(HISSING)

26:36.929 --> 26:38.214
What are you working on?

26:38.765 --> 26:40.005
No time to talk.

26:40.099 --> 26:41.839
I got to write it all down
before I forget.

26:41.934 --> 26:44.186
Yeah, I hate it when
great ideas slip away from me.

26:44.395 --> 26:45.931
They're not my ideas.

26:46.022 --> 26:48.513
They're stories from
a book that I lost.

26:49.400 --> 26:51.106
Must be a hell of a book.

26:51.319 --> 26:52.479
What's it about?

26:53.321 --> 26:54.481
Stuff.

26:55.656 --> 26:56.816
Sounds exciting.

26:56.908 --> 26:59.741
You seem awfully interested
in me and my book.

26:59.827 --> 27:01.533
Oh, I'm just being neighborly.

27:02.205 --> 27:03.786
What are you doing in Storybrooke?

27:03.998 --> 27:05.033
I'm a writer.

27:05.124 --> 27:06.079
You can write anywhere.

27:06.167 --> 27:07.907
What are you really doing here?

27:10.171 --> 27:11.160
(WHISPERS) Stuff.

27:13.800 --> 27:15.506
Good luck with the stories.

27:20.556 --> 27:22.968
Blueprints, bank statements...

27:23.059 --> 27:25.095
What is she building out there?

27:25.394 --> 27:26.770
A mansion?

27:26.896 --> 27:28.352
Well, whatever it is,
it doesn't matter.

27:29.023 --> 27:31.230
Because these escrow statements
have her name all over it.

27:31.692 --> 27:33.273
You were right. Personal use.

27:33.361 --> 27:34.976
She's done. We got her.

27:38.991 --> 27:40.947
What's wrong? Didn't you hear me?

27:41.911 --> 27:43.151
We stooped to her level.

27:43.538 --> 27:45.153
That's exactly what
I promised Henry I wouldn't do.

27:45.248 --> 27:46.863
Emma, we got her!

27:47.166 --> 27:48.702
It's fruits of the poisonous tree.

27:48.835 --> 27:50.450
Illegally obtained evidence.

27:50.545 --> 27:52.285
It'll get thrown out in court
in a heartbeat.

27:52.380 --> 27:54.120
No, we don't need her to go to jail.

27:54.215 --> 27:55.295
Then what are we doing here?

27:55.383 --> 27:56.463
What you wished for.

27:56.551 --> 27:58.633
Get everyone to see who she is.

27:58.845 --> 28:00.460
What she did to Henry
she does to everyone.

28:00.721 --> 28:02.677
She destroys what people love.

28:05.101 --> 28:06.887
Oh, let me show you something.

28:19.574 --> 28:21.030
She made me follow you.

28:21.742 --> 28:23.357
She made me tell her everything.

28:23.828 --> 28:26.410
She knew about your secret place
weeks ago.

28:26.873 --> 28:28.079
She just waited to destroy it

28:28.207 --> 28:29.993
till it would hurt
you and Henry the most.

28:31.627 --> 28:32.912
(SIGHS)

28:33.004 --> 28:34.244
It's all my fault.

28:39.510 --> 28:42.422
If you don't do this, I have to.

28:45.433 --> 28:46.513
Okay.

28:49.896 --> 28:52.729
This session of the Storybrooke
City Council will come to order.

28:53.274 --> 28:56.016
We will begin by reading
the minutes from our last meeting.

28:56.110 --> 28:58.101
Excuse me, Madam Mayor.

28:58.738 --> 29:01.605
I have something I'd like to bring to
the Council's attention.

29:02.158 --> 29:04.570
This is not an open forum, Sidney.

29:04.869 --> 29:06.951
And no one on this Council
is interested in hearing

29:07.079 --> 29:09.161
the boozy complaints of
a disgraced reporter.

29:09.624 --> 29:10.784
Now, sit down.

29:10.875 --> 29:12.331
He's not the only one
who has something to say.

29:13.419 --> 29:18.129
Miss Swan, this meeting is to
discuss issues facing Storybrooke.

29:18.257 --> 29:20.669
Like the Mayor stealing
thousands of dollars from the city

29:20.760 --> 29:21.920
to build herself a second home?

29:22.094 --> 29:23.254
(CROWD GASPING)

29:23.346 --> 29:24.586
(ALL MURMURING)

29:25.222 --> 29:27.349
(GAVEL BANGING)

29:29.644 --> 29:32.477
Miss Swan, you will sit down
immediately or so help me.

29:32.563 --> 29:33.723
What? You'll punish me?

29:33.814 --> 29:36.146
You'll bully me
like everyone else in this town?

29:36.609 --> 29:39.316
No. Not today.

29:40.029 --> 29:44.693
In my hand I am holding documents
proving that this woman, your Mayor,

29:44.825 --> 29:48.568
stole funds from the city to build herself
a lavish home in the woods.

29:48.663 --> 29:49.778
(ALL MURMURING)

29:50.957 --> 29:52.538
And this "disgraced reporter,"

29:52.625 --> 29:54.161
you wanna know why
he was really fired?

29:54.251 --> 29:56.833
Because he stood up to her.
Because he questioned her.

29:57.588 --> 30:00.500
We all know what happens to
people who question the Mayor.

30:02.218 --> 30:05.051
You claim that you act
in the best interest of all of us.

30:05.137 --> 30:06.923
But that isn't the truth, is it?

30:07.390 --> 30:09.847
The truth is, you are a thug
that doesn't care about anyone

30:09.934 --> 30:11.595
or anything but yourself.

30:11.852 --> 30:13.592
That is who you really are,

30:14.146 --> 30:16.728
and it's time for the people of
Storybrooke to know that.

30:21.487 --> 30:25.821
You are right, Miss Swan.
I am building a house.

30:31.455 --> 30:32.956
A playhouse.

30:35.209 --> 30:36.790
(ALL MURMURING)

30:37.712 --> 30:41.375
The accusations are true.
I did take city funds.

30:41.882 --> 30:44.874
I wanted to build a playground
so my son Henry,

30:45.553 --> 30:48.295
and all the children of Storybrooke,

30:48.389 --> 30:50.755
could have a special place to play.

30:51.350 --> 30:52.339
Safely.

30:54.145 --> 30:55.976
As for the sketch in your hands,

30:56.230 --> 30:58.812
it was inspired by a drawing I found

30:59.233 --> 31:01.098
in one of my son's books.

31:03.279 --> 31:05.816
So there you have it, Miss Swan.

31:05.906 --> 31:08.739
You've exposed me
for who I really am.

31:10.578 --> 31:12.409
I hope you're satisfied.

31:45.863 --> 31:47.478
(WHISPERS) Forgive me.

31:59.585 --> 32:01.325
(HISSING)

32:10.638 --> 32:12.344
(CLEARING THROAT)

32:37.414 --> 32:38.494
(HISSING)

32:39.542 --> 32:40.827
(GASPS)

32:41.877 --> 32:43.538
(CHOKING)

32:47.633 --> 32:49.134
The pain will soon pass.

32:52.888 --> 32:55.470
You asked me to find the man who
gave the mirror to your Queen.

32:56.684 --> 32:57.673
Idid.

32:58.644 --> 33:00.760
I am that man.

33:02.273 --> 33:04.138
You gave me my freedom.

33:04.233 --> 33:06.724
You gave me a chance to find love

33:06.819 --> 33:09.276
and for that
I am forever in your debt.

33:09.488 --> 33:14.152
Butjust as you freed me,
so must I now free your Queen.

33:15.911 --> 33:17.162
Forgive me.

33:17.621 --> 33:18.906
(GASPING)

33:25.421 --> 33:26.831
You were right.

33:29.550 --> 33:34.340
I never should have made a wish.

33:51.572 --> 33:53.312
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

33:54.325 --> 33:55.735
GOLD: Look at her.

33:56.285 --> 33:57.946
Queen of the castle.

33:59.455 --> 34:01.241
You know, what you did in there
was commendable, Miss Swan.

34:01.373 --> 34:04.115
But if you really want to bring her down
you're gonna need a strong ally.

34:04.919 --> 34:05.908
Like yourself?

34:06.712 --> 34:08.953
Thanks. But I'm still not interested.

34:10.090 --> 34:11.751
Oh, one can wish.

34:13.260 --> 34:15.672
Miss Swan, a word?

34:17.556 --> 34:18.545
Alone?

34:23.354 --> 34:25.811
I don't know what you were hoping to
accomplish in there,

34:26.440 --> 34:28.601
but now I hope
you'll go back to yourjob,

34:29.193 --> 34:32.401
which is upholding the law,
not breaking it.

34:33.656 --> 34:36.113
You don't think I know
you broke into my office?

34:36.659 --> 34:37.944
Don't pretend like
you're so innocent.

34:38.035 --> 34:39.775
I know you messed with
the brakes on my car.

34:39.870 --> 34:41.280
(SCOFFS) Your brakes?

34:41.789 --> 34:42.949
Are you delusional?

34:43.457 --> 34:46.574
Why would I kill you when
you just saw I had nothing to hide?

34:46.669 --> 34:47.875
Nothing I can prove.

34:47.962 --> 34:50.578
Well, until you have
something more substantial

34:50.673 --> 34:53.039
than disdain to throw my way,

34:54.301 --> 34:56.292
you're going to stay away from me.

34:57.096 --> 34:58.586
And more importantly,

34:59.014 --> 35:00.094
from Henry.

35:00.975 --> 35:03.307
-Look, that's...
-Not open for discussion.

35:04.270 --> 35:06.431
You've lost the high ground, Sheriff.

35:07.189 --> 35:09.851
If I wanted to,
there's not a judge in the world

35:09.942 --> 35:12.649
that would deny me a restraining order
after what you've done.

35:14.363 --> 35:16.820
You don't get to see my son

35:17.324 --> 35:19.110
unless I say so.

35:19.868 --> 35:21.199
And right now,

35:22.871 --> 35:24.998
I don't say so.

35:33.173 --> 35:35.084
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

35:44.810 --> 35:46.425
Why are you so far away?

35:46.729 --> 35:48.014
Come out here.

35:48.522 --> 35:49.978
EMMA: (OVER RADIO)
Sorry, kid, / canât today.

35:50.149 --> 35:53.266
You're undercover, aren't you?
For Operation Cobra?

35:53.736 --> 35:56.068
No, Henry, Iâm not undercover.

35:56.780 --> 35:59.897
Your mom, she doesnât want us
seeing each other for a while.

36:00.034 --> 36:01.274
You don't have to listen to her.

36:01.368 --> 36:03.359
Actually, this time I do.

36:04.538 --> 36:05.994
I screwed up, Henry.

36:06.665 --> 36:09.577
/ got mad at your mom, about you
and the book and everything, and...

36:12.755 --> 36:15.417
Well, we âre just gonna have to
be apart for a little while.

36:15.758 --> 36:17.214
I don't wanna be apart.

36:17.301 --> 36:19.917
Neither do I.
But right now, we have to.

36:20.512 --> 36:22.673
Don ât worry, Iâll ï¬nd a way back in.

36:22.806 --> 36:27.721
And hey, if it's out there, Henry,
I will find your book.

36:28.145 --> 36:29.305
Good luck.

36:29.480 --> 36:32.472
It's probably gone
and it's probably never coming back.

36:36.904 --> 36:38.144
(STARTS ENGINE)

37:25.411 --> 37:27.618
Looks like we had the same idea.

37:27.704 --> 37:31.288
Well, if you can't beat her, drink.

37:36.296 --> 37:37.502
(SIGHS)

37:37.589 --> 37:38.840
How did we not see this?

37:38.924 --> 37:41.381
We did.
We saw it all, right from the start.

37:42.261 --> 37:45.503
We just didn't want to look.
Blinded by our anger.

37:46.640 --> 37:48.141
By everything.

37:49.351 --> 37:50.636
This time.

37:52.813 --> 37:55.555
But there are a lot more skeletons
in Regina's closet.

37:56.108 --> 37:57.848
And the good news?

37:59.027 --> 38:00.892
You got yourself an ally.

38:05.701 --> 38:07.692
We won't get fooled again.

38:12.207 --> 38:15.324
It is done.
You're free, my love.

38:15.794 --> 38:18.877
We are free to be together at last.

38:20.174 --> 38:24.133
Did you not hear me?
Our days of imprisonment are over.

38:24.636 --> 38:26.376
You haven't heard the news.

38:28.724 --> 38:33.343
The palace guards found the snake.
They know it's from your country.

38:33.437 --> 38:35.143
They know it was you
who killed the King.

38:37.441 --> 38:39.727
It's only a matter of time
before they catch you.

38:41.195 --> 38:43.106
You will be executed.

38:45.908 --> 38:47.114
I'm sorry,

38:49.077 --> 38:51.068
but we will never be together.

38:51.580 --> 38:53.787
Come. I've arranged for a boat

38:53.874 --> 38:55.956
to provide you safe passage
out of the Kingdom.

38:56.251 --> 38:57.957
You must leave at once.

39:02.883 --> 39:05.374
The Agrabahn viper.

39:07.221 --> 39:10.634
Of all the snakes in all the world,

39:10.849 --> 39:12.635
that is what you chose.

39:17.523 --> 39:20.515
You wanted the murder to
be traced back to me.

39:21.860 --> 39:25.648
You... You fooled me.

39:26.615 --> 39:28.571
You never loved me.

39:31.286 --> 39:32.901
Loved you?

39:35.541 --> 39:38.908
Iwanted the King killed
and you killed him.

39:40.045 --> 39:42.502
You are no longer of any use to me.

39:44.049 --> 39:47.132
Be grateful
I'm offering you an escape.

39:48.679 --> 39:51.091
Now, flee the Kingdom
and never turn back.

39:53.392 --> 39:55.633
I can't live without you.

39:57.521 --> 39:58.931
I won't live without you.

39:59.064 --> 40:01.476
Did you not understand me?

40:01.775 --> 40:03.436
I don't love you.

40:04.236 --> 40:06.852
There is no way
we will ever be together.

40:09.825 --> 40:11.486
There is one way.

40:15.789 --> 40:18.872
There is still one wish remaining.

40:19.251 --> 40:23.665
I wish to be with you forever.

40:24.256 --> 40:28.124
To look upon your face always,
to never leave your side.

40:32.931 --> 40:34.046
(GASPS)

40:34.933 --> 40:36.093
MIRROR: N0!

40:37.519 --> 40:38.679
No!

40:40.772 --> 40:43.980
No!

40:45.819 --> 40:48.310
Well, looks like you got your wish.

40:48.989 --> 40:50.854
You will be with me,

40:51.658 --> 40:53.944
forever.

41:04.755 --> 41:06.586
Have a seat, Sidney.

41:13.347 --> 41:14.553
(SIGHS)

41:24.483 --> 41:25.893
Well?

41:29.655 --> 41:32.397
SIDNEY: (ON TAPE)
You got yourself an ally.

41:32.491 --> 41:34.356
EMMA: (ON TAPE)
We won ât get fooled again.

41:34.826 --> 41:36.032
(LAUGHS)

41:36.119 --> 41:37.154
She bought it.

41:37.329 --> 41:38.694
-All of it.
-(CHUCKLES)

41:40.082 --> 41:41.697
Masterful job, Sidney.

41:42.334 --> 41:43.494
Top to bottom.

41:44.044 --> 41:46.751
And cutting the brakes on her car?
(CHUCKLES)

41:47.589 --> 41:48.704
Inspued.

41:48.924 --> 41:50.505
I'm glad you approve.

41:50.759 --> 41:54.593
Now she trusts you.
Now we can have some fun.

41:54.680 --> 41:58.969
Everything she does,
everywhere she goes,

41:59.059 --> 42:00.424
you'll know about it.

42:00.560 --> 42:01.970
Oh.

42:06.983 --> 42:09.895
I don't know what
I'd do without you, Sidney.
